1
00:00:04,166 --> 00:00:07,700
[♪]

2
00:01:04,433 --> 00:01:08,066
ROBOT:
Once upon a time,
in a castle far, far away,

3
00:01:08,100 --> 00:01:10,433
there lived
a beautiful princess.

4
00:01:10,466 --> 00:01:12,466
She had everything she wanted,

5
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:15,200
and yet she was very lonely.

6
00:01:15,233 --> 00:01:18,333
Then, one day,
something strange and wonderful

7
00:01:18,366 --> 00:01:20,300
fluttered into
the castle garden.

8
00:01:20,333 --> 00:01:22,066
Was it a happy butterfly?

9
00:01:22,100 --> 00:01:24,100
Was it a lost nightingale?

10
00:01:24,133 --> 00:01:26,333
Oh, my, no!

11
00:01:26,366 --> 00:01:28,200
It was something magical.

12
00:01:28,233 --> 00:01:31,466
Something with three antennas.

13
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:34,533
Can you guess what it was?
Can you?

14
00:01:34,566 --> 00:01:36,600
[YELPS]

15
00:01:36,633 --> 00:01:38,366
Cut to the chase, Friday!

16
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:40,100
Now, what in the world was it?

17
00:01:40,133 --> 00:01:42,300
Nina!

18
00:01:42,333 --> 00:01:44,366
I was just
getting to that!

19
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:46,400
Well, then
get to it quicker!

20
00:01:46,433 --> 00:01:48,333
I'm getting older
by the minute, you know?

21
00:01:48,366 --> 00:01:50,100
Nina, try to be
a little more patient.

22
00:01:50,133 --> 00:01:51,666
Where were we?

23
00:01:51,700 --> 00:01:53,533
Oh, that's right.

24
00:01:53,566 --> 00:01:57,133
The creature with three antennas
was a pigwidgin!

25
00:01:57,166 --> 00:01:58,633
Pigwidgin?

26
00:01:58,666 --> 00:02:00,333
[LAUGHS]

27
00:02:00,366 --> 00:02:01,633
What a stupid-sounding word!

28
00:02:01,666 --> 00:02:02,666
You made that up!

29
00:02:02,700 --> 00:02:03,766
Hey!

30
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:05,533
What's this thing?

31
00:02:05,566 --> 00:02:07,500
The three antennas
of a pigwidgin,

32
00:02:07,533 --> 00:02:09,433
a magical flying fairy.

33
00:02:09,466 --> 00:02:11,366
Oh, there is
no such thing!

34
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:13,533
The first antenna
can find love,

35
00:02:13,566 --> 00:02:16,466
the second antenna
can find friendship,

36
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:17,766
and the third one
can find--

37
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:19,666
[SCREAMS]

38
00:02:19,700 --> 00:02:21,666
So let me guess.

39
00:02:21,700 --> 00:02:24,166
A robot
who's not boring.

40
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:26,033
[CLEARS THROAT]

41
00:02:26,066 --> 00:02:28,800
And the third one
can help you find your dreams.

42
00:02:28,833 --> 00:02:31,633
A pigwidgin can grant
your every wish.

43
00:02:31,666 --> 00:02:32,733
Yeah?
[PHONE RINGS]

44
00:02:32,766 --> 00:02:37,666
Yes. And so
the lonely princess was--

45
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:40,400
<i>Happy birthday, Nina!</i>

46
00:02:40,433 --> 00:02:42,200
Did you like
all the birthday presents

47
00:02:42,233 --> 00:02:43,733
Daddy asked his secretary
to send you?

48
00:02:43,766 --> 00:02:46,233
Uh, I guess so.

49
00:02:46,266 --> 00:02:49,200
But didn't I give you

50
00:02:49,233 --> 00:02:51,700
every single thing
you asked for, sweetheart?

51
00:02:51,733 --> 00:02:53,600
What about the custom-made
giraffe umbrella

52
00:02:53,633 --> 00:02:56,066
or the solid gold
skateboard

53
00:02:56,100 --> 00:02:57,766
or Friday,
the storyteller robot?

54
00:02:57,800 --> 00:02:59,566
Boring!

55
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:01,500
Been there,
played with that!

56
00:03:01,533 --> 00:03:03,233
And Friday just tells
stupid stories.

57
00:03:03,266 --> 00:03:06,633
<i>Well, then, what is it</i>
<i>you do want, my darling?</i>

58
00:03:06,666 --> 00:03:08,700
<i>Tell me! I'll get you</i>
<i>anything money can buy.</i>

59
00:03:08,733 --> 00:03:10,033
[SIGHS]

60
00:03:10,066 --> 00:03:11,200
What I want is...

61
00:03:11,233 --> 00:03:13,166
What I want...

62
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:14,200
DADDY:
Yes?

63
00:03:16,533 --> 00:03:17,733
A pigwidgin!

64
00:03:17,766 --> 00:03:18,766
A what?

65
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:20,400
It's a kind of fairy.

66
00:03:20,433 --> 00:03:23,066
If you really love me,
that's what you'll get me.

67
00:03:23,100 --> 00:03:24,166
<i>Uh, but, Nina--</i>

68
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:26,100
That'll teach him!

69
00:03:26,133 --> 00:03:29,100
Daddy never ever comes home
to play with me.

70
00:03:29,133 --> 00:03:30,533
He's always working.

71
00:03:30,566 --> 00:03:31,633
FRIDAY:
Nina...

72
00:03:31,666 --> 00:03:33,133
now I finally
understand.

73
00:03:33,166 --> 00:03:34,700
Huh?

74
00:03:34,733 --> 00:03:36,733
You should have told me
that that was
what you wanted.

75
00:03:36,766 --> 00:03:38,333
Huh?

76
00:03:38,366 --> 00:03:41,466
I've got an idea
that will fix everything!

77
00:03:47,574 --> 00:03:49,140
ABERCROMBIE:
Nail it down
good and tight!

78
00:03:49,174 --> 00:03:51,140
I don't want any doors
falling off!

79
00:03:51,174 --> 00:03:53,274
[LAUGHS]

80
00:03:53,307 --> 00:03:54,607
All right!

81
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:56,507
Phase two of my tree house
is looking good!

82
00:03:56,540 --> 00:03:58,474
Hey, why is it
your tree house?

83
00:03:58,507 --> 00:04:00,340
We're the ones who are
doing all the work!

84
00:04:00,374 --> 00:04:01,674
You haven't
done anything!

85
00:04:01,707 --> 00:04:03,640
Yeah, that's 'cause

86
00:04:03,674 --> 00:04:06,007
I am the idea guy,
the one with the vision.

87
00:04:06,040 --> 00:04:09,040
All you clowns gotta do
is follow my blueprints.

88
00:04:09,074 --> 00:04:11,007
A monkey could build this thing!

89
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:13,074
Why not?
A monkey designed it.

90
00:04:13,107 --> 00:04:14,907
We need some more vines.

91
00:04:14,940 --> 00:04:16,574
Astro went to the park
to get some more.

92
00:04:19,374 --> 00:04:21,007
[GRUNTS]

93
00:04:21,040 --> 00:04:22,007
Huh?

94
00:04:25,074 --> 00:04:27,574
What is it?

95
00:04:27,607 --> 00:04:29,074
[YELLS]

96
00:04:29,107 --> 00:04:30,440
[GRUNTS]
[GROANS]

97
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:34,207
I did it! I did it!
I finally caught one!

98
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:36,374
Uh, is there something
I can help you with?

99
00:04:36,407 --> 00:04:38,540
Hmm?

100
00:04:38,574 --> 00:04:41,340
Aah! You're not
a pigwidgin!

101
00:04:41,374 --> 00:04:43,474
You emit
a non-human frequency,

102
00:04:43,507 --> 00:04:46,407
but you're bigger
and heavier and you don't
have any wings!

103
00:04:46,440 --> 00:04:47,907
I'm sorry.

104
00:04:47,940 --> 00:04:50,174
No, I'm not a
pigwidge...whatever.

105
00:04:50,207 --> 00:04:52,040
I'm Astro. Who are you?

106
00:04:52,074 --> 00:04:54,040
BOYS:
Friday?

107
00:04:54,074 --> 00:04:55,074
Mm-hm. That's me.

108
00:04:55,107 --> 00:04:57,974
I'm a storyteller robot.

109
00:04:58,007 --> 00:05:01,107
I'm programmed with fairy tales
from all over the world.

110
00:05:01,140 --> 00:05:02,907
Hey, cool job!

111
00:05:02,940 --> 00:05:05,940
So is that why
you're looking for
a pigwidgin?

112
00:05:05,974 --> 00:05:09,207
It's going to be
a gift for a lonely
little girl I know.

113
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:10,574
ABERCROMBIE:
Oh, baloney!

114
00:05:10,607 --> 00:05:12,274
Fairy tales
are bogus!

115
00:05:12,307 --> 00:05:14,140
They are not!

116
00:05:14,174 --> 00:05:17,340
Yeah, Friday.
Who believes in wizards
and elves and pixies?

117
00:05:17,374 --> 00:05:20,574
I agree. Magical
creatures like those
are purely fictional.

118
00:05:20,607 --> 00:05:22,074
[SHRIEKS]

119
00:05:22,107 --> 00:05:24,540
Three more fairy folk
have just vanished!

120
00:05:24,574 --> 00:05:25,940
BOYS:
What?

121
00:05:25,974 --> 00:05:26,874
It's true!

122
00:05:26,907 --> 00:05:29,040
Fairies and gnomes
and pigwidgins are born

123
00:05:29,074 --> 00:05:30,974
whenever
a child smiles.

124
00:05:31,007 --> 00:05:33,274
But whenever a child says
he doesn't believe,

125
00:05:33,307 --> 00:05:35,940
one of them
disappears forever!

126
00:05:35,974 --> 00:05:37,507
Friday,
wait!

127
00:05:37,540 --> 00:05:40,607
What do these magical
creatures look like?

128
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:43,074
Well, of course,
there are many
different kinds.

129
00:05:43,107 --> 00:05:44,207
[CLEARS THROAT]

130
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:47,174
Now, the ones that live
in the water are called mermaids

131
00:05:47,207 --> 00:05:49,640
and they have fish tails
instead of legs.

132
00:05:49,674 --> 00:05:52,140
In a forest, there are
the gnomes and the elves.

133
00:05:52,174 --> 00:05:54,074
In a garden,

134
00:05:54,107 --> 00:05:57,274
you'll find singing sprites
for the musically inclined.

135
00:05:57,307 --> 00:06:00,340
While the fog phantoms
hardly have any shape at all.

136
00:06:00,374 --> 00:06:02,140
And then there are
many, many others.

137
00:06:02,172 --> 00:06:03,782
BOYS:
Wow!

138
00:06:03,921 --> 00:06:05,154
Of course,
if you don't want to

139
00:06:05,188 --> 00:06:07,021
help me find one,
I'll understand.

140
00:06:07,054 --> 00:06:07,854
ALEJO:
Well...

141
00:06:10,221 --> 00:06:11,754
ASTRO:
<i>I don't get it.</i>

142
00:06:11,788 --> 00:06:13,788
<i>Why are we searching</i>
<i>the City Hall attic?</i>

143
00:06:13,821 --> 00:06:15,821
FRIDAY:
<i>Well, pigwidgins are</i>
<i>very civic-minded</i>

144
00:06:15,854 --> 00:06:18,154
and they love
the dark.

145
00:06:18,188 --> 00:06:20,521
I haven't
seen anything yet.

146
00:06:20,554 --> 00:06:21,988
They're
very good hiders.

147
00:06:24,221 --> 00:06:27,188
Alejo, do you think
they really could exist?

148
00:06:27,221 --> 00:06:29,421
Scientifically,
it's highly improbable.

149
00:06:29,454 --> 00:06:31,754
ABERCROMBIE:
Scientifically,
this is nutso.

150
00:06:31,788 --> 00:06:33,721
We should be building
our tree house!

151
00:06:33,754 --> 00:06:35,821
I'm sensing
a strange frequency!

152
00:06:35,854 --> 00:06:38,854
Up ahead in the darkness,
something not quite human!

153
00:06:41,621 --> 00:06:44,721
[ALL SCREAMING]

154
00:06:44,754 --> 00:06:46,554
Bats!

155
00:06:46,588 --> 00:06:48,621
ABERCROMBIE:
I hate bats!

156
00:06:48,654 --> 00:06:49,654
[FRIDAY SHRIEKS]

157
00:06:51,821 --> 00:06:54,521
Well,
that went well.

158
00:06:54,554 --> 00:06:57,054
What did you expect? I told you
there was no such thing as--

159
00:06:57,088 --> 00:06:58,488
Shhh!

160
00:06:58,521 --> 00:06:59,721
You'd better not say it,

161
00:06:59,754 --> 00:07:02,888
or a pixie or elf
or something might vanish.

162
00:07:02,921 --> 00:07:04,621
He's right.

163
00:07:04,654 --> 00:07:08,121
You're gonna vanish if we don't
finish this tree house!

164
00:07:08,154 --> 00:07:11,121
MAN:
It is finished,
just as you ordered.

165
00:07:11,154 --> 00:07:11,921
Now, shall
we try it?

166
00:07:13,688 --> 00:07:16,754
[MACHINE HUMS]

167
00:07:29,054 --> 00:07:30,588
Friday!

168
00:07:30,621 --> 00:07:32,454
Uh!
Gotcha!

169
00:07:32,488 --> 00:07:35,054
Where have you
been sneaking out to
every day? Don't deny it!

170
00:07:35,088 --> 00:07:37,954
Actually, I'm trying
to catch a pigwidgin.

171
00:07:37,988 --> 00:07:39,788
A pigwidgin?

172
00:07:39,821 --> 00:07:42,621
But that's what
I told Daddy I wanted.

173
00:07:42,654 --> 00:07:45,688
Is it for me?

174
00:07:45,721 --> 00:07:48,488
Thank you, Friday!
You're the best!

175
00:07:48,521 --> 00:07:49,654
Oh, Nina.

176
00:07:49,688 --> 00:07:53,688
[BOTH SHRIEK]

177
00:07:53,721 --> 00:07:58,088
I'll be back soon, Nina.
You stay here
and be a good girl.

178
00:07:58,121 --> 00:08:00,554
FRIDAY:
Are we ready to catch
a pigwidgin, men?

179
00:08:00,588 --> 00:08:02,021
Whoosh! Pow!

180
00:08:02,054 --> 00:08:03,654
Hey!

181
00:08:03,688 --> 00:08:05,054
We'll swoop down
on 'em

182
00:08:05,088 --> 00:08:06,954
and catch 'em
before they know
what hit 'em!

183
00:08:06,988 --> 00:08:07,788
Yeah!

184
00:08:09,121 --> 00:08:11,421
No?

185
00:08:11,454 --> 00:08:13,754
You know, I'm getting
sick and tired

186
00:08:13,788 --> 00:08:16,721
of listening to you
yammering on about fairies.

187
00:08:16,754 --> 00:08:19,588
Right! So let's be off,
fearless fairy hunters!

188
00:08:19,621 --> 00:08:21,721
Why don't you be off,
and we'll catch up?

189
00:08:21,754 --> 00:08:22,788
[GIRL GRUNTS]

190
00:08:22,821 --> 00:08:23,788
BOTH:
Huh?

191
00:08:26,221 --> 00:08:27,721
Phew!

192
00:08:27,754 --> 00:08:29,421
All right, next time
I come here,

193
00:08:29,454 --> 00:08:30,754
there'd better be
an elevator!

194
00:08:30,788 --> 00:08:33,988
These goofs are the best
you could round up?

195
00:08:34,021 --> 00:08:35,754
Excuse me,
who are you?

196
00:08:35,788 --> 00:08:37,521
Nina!
BOYS:
Huh?

197
00:08:37,554 --> 00:08:39,688
You followed me here,
didn't you?

198
00:08:39,721 --> 00:08:41,188
[GIGGLES]

199
00:08:41,221 --> 00:08:43,154
You must be the little girl

200
00:08:43,188 --> 00:08:45,421
who wants Friday
to catch her a pigwidgin.

201
00:08:45,454 --> 00:08:46,421
Bingo!

202
00:08:46,454 --> 00:08:47,788
So let's get started.
Now!

203
00:08:55,954 --> 00:08:57,554
FRIDAY:
<i>All magical creatures</i>

204
00:08:57,588 --> 00:09:00,921
respond to the vibrational
frequencies of Mother Earth,

205
00:09:00,954 --> 00:09:03,088
which is why one commonly finds

206
00:09:03,121 --> 00:09:05,488
their nests and dwellings
deep underground.

207
00:09:06,888 --> 00:09:08,454
Oh!

208
00:09:08,488 --> 00:09:10,521
My shoes!
They're ruined!

209
00:09:10,554 --> 00:09:12,721
It's just
water.

210
00:09:12,754 --> 00:09:16,188
It's dirty and it's wet,
and I hate it!

211
00:09:16,221 --> 00:09:18,521
[LAUGHING]

212
00:09:18,554 --> 00:09:19,588
Maybe you should have
known better

213
00:09:19,621 --> 00:09:22,788
than to wear your
fancy-schmancy shoes down here.

214
00:09:22,821 --> 00:09:24,954
Halt, speed bump!
What?

215
00:09:26,221 --> 00:09:27,521
Speak up!

216
00:09:27,554 --> 00:09:28,554
[WHISPERING]

217
00:09:28,588 --> 00:09:29,788
I can't hear you.

218
00:09:29,821 --> 00:09:32,021
Carry me,
you idiot!

219
00:09:32,054 --> 00:09:34,621
Are you cracked?
Why would I do that?

220
00:09:34,654 --> 00:09:37,154
Because I'm not walking
another step until you do.

221
00:09:37,188 --> 00:09:38,988
Like I care!

222
00:09:39,021 --> 00:09:40,821
Calm down,
Abercrombie.

223
00:09:40,854 --> 00:09:42,588
Nina,
I'll carry you.

224
00:09:42,621 --> 00:09:43,388
Humph!

225
00:09:46,921 --> 00:09:49,188
Are you sure
it's no trouble, Astro?

226
00:09:49,221 --> 00:09:52,421
I'm fine.
Funny hair!

227
00:09:52,454 --> 00:09:54,088
Nina, could you
not do that?

228
00:09:54,121 --> 00:09:56,021
Astro's way too nice.

229
00:09:56,054 --> 00:09:57,088
[LAUGHS]

230
00:09:57,121 --> 00:09:58,121
Hmm?

231
00:09:58,154 --> 00:09:59,788
Something's
coming!

232
00:09:59,821 --> 00:10:01,054
Is it a fairy?

233
00:10:01,088 --> 00:10:02,788
Maybe
it's a pigwidgin!

234
00:10:04,821 --> 00:10:06,821
[MONSTER LAUGHING]

235
00:10:06,854 --> 00:10:08,121
[ALL GASP]

236
00:10:10,588 --> 00:10:12,588
Was that a fairy?

237
00:10:12,621 --> 00:10:14,054
That's-- That's...

238
00:10:14,088 --> 00:10:16,521
Ever seen anything
like that?

239
00:10:16,554 --> 00:10:18,554
ALEJO:
Yeah, I have.
But where?

240
00:10:18,588 --> 00:10:20,521
Right here!
Huh?

241
00:10:20,554 --> 00:10:22,554
ALEJO:
He's right!
That's it!

242
00:10:22,588 --> 00:10:23,854
Here it comes again!

243
00:10:23,888 --> 00:10:26,554
[MONSTER LAUGHING]

244
00:10:26,588 --> 00:10:27,588
[BOTH SCREAM]

245
00:10:27,621 --> 00:10:30,454
That is definitely not a fairy.

246
00:10:30,488 --> 00:10:32,421
[LAUGHING]

247
00:10:32,454 --> 00:10:33,788
[SCREAMS]

248
00:10:33,821 --> 00:10:34,688
Hold still,
you monster!

249
00:10:34,721 --> 00:10:37,188
I'll get you! I'll get you!

250
00:10:37,221 --> 00:10:40,154
W-w-what is that?
It's yucky!

251
00:10:40,188 --> 00:10:42,154
[FRIDAY GRUNTS]

252
00:10:42,188 --> 00:10:43,921
Aah! Run, Astro!

253
00:10:46,721 --> 00:10:48,388
[SCREAMS]

254
00:10:49,688 --> 00:10:51,654
Hey, this thing's
just a hologram.

255
00:10:51,688 --> 00:10:54,388
Who cares?
Make it go away now!

256
00:10:56,121 --> 00:10:57,721
It's gone!

257
00:10:57,754 --> 00:10:59,921
So am I, home!
Now, step on it!

258
00:10:59,954 --> 00:11:02,521
[SIRENS WAILING]

259
00:11:05,788 --> 00:11:06,754
Huh?

260
00:11:13,088 --> 00:11:15,154
Detective Tawashi!

261
00:11:15,188 --> 00:11:16,488
Astro.

262
00:11:16,521 --> 00:11:18,154
Did something
happen here?
Sure did.

263
00:11:18,188 --> 00:11:20,621
The owner of this
jewelry store was attacked,

264
00:11:20,654 --> 00:11:22,088
and the store was robbed.

265
00:11:22,121 --> 00:11:25,188
She said it was
some kind of monster.

266
00:11:25,221 --> 00:11:26,888
Monster?

267
00:11:26,921 --> 00:11:30,521
Us too! A big-old, ugly
green thing chased us!

268
00:11:30,554 --> 00:11:32,654
What was that?
Astro, is that true?

269
00:11:32,688 --> 00:11:33,688
Yes, sir.

270
00:11:33,721 --> 00:11:35,154
Hmm.

271
00:11:35,188 --> 00:11:36,588
There have been
five reports today

272
00:11:36,621 --> 00:11:39,054
of people attacked
by monsters.

273
00:11:39,088 --> 00:11:41,588
And while the victims
run away in terror,

274
00:11:41,621 --> 00:11:44,488
expensive items
mysteriously disappear.

275
00:11:44,521 --> 00:11:46,188
Detective!

276
00:11:46,221 --> 00:11:48,688
Please catch
that awful thing quickly!

277
00:11:48,721 --> 00:11:50,188
I can't get the memory

278
00:11:50,221 --> 00:11:52,854
of that horrible creature
out of my mind.

279
00:11:52,888 --> 00:11:54,588
Strange, but
it looked so much

280
00:11:54,621 --> 00:11:56,988
like a dog that chased me
when I was just a child.

281
00:11:57,021 --> 00:11:59,121
Hey, the monster
that attacked us

282
00:11:59,154 --> 00:12:00,721
looked just like
Abercrombie's drawing!

283
00:12:00,754 --> 00:12:02,554
Uh-huh!

284
00:12:02,588 --> 00:12:06,154
The dog from her childhood,
the monster Abercrombie drew...

285
00:12:06,188 --> 00:12:08,854
Both of the images
came from their minds.

286
00:12:08,888 --> 00:12:11,021
So what are you saying?

287
00:12:11,054 --> 00:12:13,988
Something must be taking
the images from their thoughts

288
00:12:14,021 --> 00:12:16,454
and projecting them
as holograms.

289
00:12:16,488 --> 00:12:19,521
I think maybe that's where all
the monsters are coming from.

290
00:12:19,554 --> 00:12:21,421
But who would be
capable of that?

291
00:12:21,454 --> 00:12:22,821
I don't know.

292
00:12:22,854 --> 00:12:24,421
But it'd have to be someone

293
00:12:24,454 --> 00:12:26,921
very ruthless
and very, very smart.

294
00:12:26,954 --> 00:12:31,521
Uh...so you're telling me that
monster came out of my mind?

295
00:12:31,554 --> 00:12:32,788
Then it's your fault!

296
00:12:32,821 --> 00:12:34,188
Huh?

297
00:12:34,221 --> 00:12:36,454
You dreamed up
that awful thing
on purpose

298
00:12:36,488 --> 00:12:38,721
just to
frighten me because
you don't like me!

299
00:12:38,754 --> 00:12:40,854
No, I didn't!
What are you talking about?

300
00:12:40,888 --> 00:12:41,921
I'm out of here!
Hey, wait!

301
00:12:41,954 --> 00:12:43,788
FRIDAY:
Nina, wait!

302
00:12:47,854 --> 00:12:50,921
[LAUGHING]

303
00:12:58,619 --> 00:13:00,589
Nina, please!
Open the door!

304
00:13:00,622 --> 00:13:01,955
Nina!

305
00:13:02,437 --> 00:13:04,895
Go away! Leave me alone!

306
00:13:04,928 --> 00:13:06,195
Phooey!

307
00:13:06,228 --> 00:13:08,861
I hate you
and all your dumb friends!

308
00:13:08,895 --> 00:13:11,928
If the monsters
in my mind turn real,

309
00:13:11,961 --> 00:13:13,061
I'll have them
stomp the whole city.

310
00:13:13,095 --> 00:13:14,228
Huh?

311
00:13:17,028 --> 00:13:18,461
What are those?

312
00:13:20,595 --> 00:13:21,895
Fairies?

313
00:13:21,928 --> 00:13:23,061
ASTRO:
Nina!

314
00:13:23,095 --> 00:13:24,128
Astro!

315
00:13:24,161 --> 00:13:25,595
How do you like
the fairies?

316
00:13:25,628 --> 00:13:27,928
Me and the other guys
made them just for you.

317
00:13:27,961 --> 00:13:30,061
For me?
Sure!

318
00:13:30,095 --> 00:13:32,861
ABERCROMBIE: Hey!
Oh!

319
00:13:32,895 --> 00:13:34,895
[GRUNTS]

320
00:13:34,928 --> 00:13:36,528
Nina!

321
00:13:36,561 --> 00:13:39,028
Why'd you do this?
Tell me!

322
00:13:39,061 --> 00:13:41,395
Because I'm sorry
my drawing scared you.

323
00:13:41,428 --> 00:13:43,261
It scared me too.
Ha-ha!

324
00:13:43,295 --> 00:13:45,561
You wanna go
fairy hunting again?

325
00:13:45,595 --> 00:13:47,061
Really?

326
00:13:47,095 --> 00:13:50,528
Uh, I mean, I really
can't waste my time

327
00:13:50,561 --> 00:13:53,028
on such childish things
as chasing fairies.

328
00:13:53,061 --> 00:13:55,561
Nina, we're going
to go fairy hunting.

329
00:13:55,595 --> 00:13:57,528
Are you coming or not?

330
00:13:57,561 --> 00:14:01,328
Well, I suppose if you insist.
It would be rude not to.

331
00:14:01,361 --> 00:14:02,161
FRIDAY:
Then we're off!

332
00:14:02,195 --> 00:14:03,195
Whoa!

333
00:14:03,228 --> 00:14:05,895
Woo-hoo!

334
00:14:05,928 --> 00:14:08,028
[LAUGHING]

335
00:14:08,061 --> 00:14:10,128
The fearless fairy hunters
ride again!

336
00:14:10,161 --> 00:14:11,128
Yahoo!

337
00:14:14,128 --> 00:14:14,961
Nina!

338
00:14:14,995 --> 00:14:16,828
Daddy!

339
00:14:16,861 --> 00:14:17,861
Nina!

340
00:14:17,895 --> 00:14:20,161
[BOTH LAUGHING]

341
00:14:20,195 --> 00:14:23,961
I've got a big surprise
for you. Something
you really wanted.

342
00:14:23,995 --> 00:14:25,595
Really?
Well, what is it?

343
00:14:25,628 --> 00:14:27,461
It's coming today
and it's expensive.

344
00:14:27,495 --> 00:14:29,428
Your very own fairy!

345
00:14:29,461 --> 00:14:30,461
What?

346
00:14:30,495 --> 00:14:33,028
Sir, you bought
a fairy?

347
00:14:33,061 --> 00:14:34,228
Of course.

348
00:14:34,261 --> 00:14:35,895
Why, there's nothing
in this world

349
00:14:35,928 --> 00:14:37,128
that you can't buy
with enough money.

350
00:14:39,361 --> 00:14:42,895
Oh, Daddy! How could you?

351
00:14:42,928 --> 00:14:44,061
You've ruined everything!

352
00:14:44,095 --> 00:14:45,295
Nina!

353
00:14:47,261 --> 00:14:48,395
But...what did I say?

354
00:14:48,428 --> 00:14:49,495
ASTRO:
I think she wants to

355
00:14:49,528 --> 00:14:51,528
find her own fairy
with her new friends.

356
00:14:51,561 --> 00:14:54,495
Huh?
Sir, how could you
buy a fairy?

357
00:14:54,528 --> 00:14:56,928
Oh, it's
not real.

358
00:14:56,961 --> 00:15:00,128
I had a machine
created that could
project a hologram

359
00:15:00,161 --> 00:15:02,028
from the image
of a fairy
in Nina's mind.

360
00:15:02,061 --> 00:15:03,895
<i>If she could imagine a fairy,</i>

361
00:15:03,928 --> 00:15:06,528
<i>the machine</i>
<i>could make it seem real.</i>

362
00:15:06,561 --> 00:15:09,561
That's awesome! Did you
design this machine yourself?

363
00:15:09,595 --> 00:15:13,161
Er, no. A strange little man
approached me with the idea.

364
00:15:13,195 --> 00:15:14,328
He called himself...

365
00:15:14,361 --> 00:15:17,595
<i>Dr. Minimini.</i>

366
00:15:17,628 --> 00:15:19,961
Dr. Minimini?
He's no good!

367
00:15:19,995 --> 00:15:21,028
What?

368
00:15:21,061 --> 00:15:22,261
DR. O'SHAY:
Astro, are you there?

369
00:15:23,595 --> 00:15:25,095
Yes, doctor?

370
00:15:25,128 --> 00:15:26,261
<i>You're needed at once.</i>

371
00:15:26,295 --> 00:15:28,261
<i>The Central Bank</i>
<i>is swarming with monsters.</i>

372
00:15:28,295 --> 00:15:29,528
What?

373
00:15:29,561 --> 00:15:31,161
I just got a call
from the police.

374
00:15:31,195 --> 00:15:32,928
They said monsters

375
00:15:32,961 --> 00:15:35,495
are appearing out of thin air
and attacking everyone!

376
00:15:35,528 --> 00:15:38,195
<i>Doctor, tell them to look</i>
<i>for a machine nearby.</i>

377
00:15:38,228 --> 00:15:39,928
A machine?

378
00:15:39,961 --> 00:15:42,228
<i>Yes, a device</i>
<i>that can take</i>

379
00:15:42,261 --> 00:15:43,995
<i>mental images</i>
<i>and make them visible.</i>

380
00:15:44,028 --> 00:15:47,028
But who in the world
would build something like that?

381
00:15:47,061 --> 00:15:48,228
Dr. Minimini.

382
00:15:48,261 --> 00:15:49,461
What?

383
00:15:49,495 --> 00:15:51,861
I heard Minimini
broke out of prison

384
00:15:51,895 --> 00:15:53,128
and is still
on the loose.

385
00:15:53,161 --> 00:15:55,161
Could he be up to
his old tricks?

386
00:15:55,195 --> 00:15:57,395
[SIRENS WAILING]

387
00:16:01,261 --> 00:16:02,295
[SOBBING]

388
00:16:02,328 --> 00:16:03,861
Nina?

389
00:16:03,895 --> 00:16:05,561
Daddy just doesn't get it.

390
00:16:06,995 --> 00:16:13,639
He thinks all I want
are things...you can buy!

391
00:16:13,672 --> 00:16:15,372
But he's wrong!

392
00:16:15,405 --> 00:16:17,614
Nina, nobody
bought us, and
we're your friends.

393
00:16:17,975 --> 00:16:19,986
What?
He's right!

394
00:16:20,019 --> 00:16:22,752
Yeah, we're here just
because we like you,

395
00:16:22,786 --> 00:16:24,886
and your dad didn't
have to pay us
anything at all.

396
00:16:24,919 --> 00:16:26,986
We're really...friends?

397
00:16:27,019 --> 00:16:30,119
ABERCROMBIE:
Sure! Fearless fairy hunters
stick together!

398
00:16:30,152 --> 00:16:31,919
Yeah!

399
00:16:31,952 --> 00:16:32,952
[GASPS]

400
00:16:32,986 --> 00:16:35,152
ALL:
A fairy!

401
00:16:35,186 --> 00:16:37,052
NINA:
A fairy
with three antennas!

402
00:16:37,086 --> 00:16:39,686
It's a real live pigwidgin!

403
00:16:42,552 --> 00:16:44,119
[SCREAMS]

404
00:16:44,152 --> 00:16:47,152
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

405
00:16:55,552 --> 00:16:57,519
What in the world
is going on in here?

406
00:17:01,986 --> 00:17:04,252
[CACKLING]

407
00:17:04,286 --> 00:17:06,786
Run, run,
you ignorant fools!

408
00:17:06,819 --> 00:17:09,186
You're all just running
from your own worst fears!

409
00:17:09,219 --> 00:17:12,886
All my machine does is help you
see what they look like.

410
00:17:12,919 --> 00:17:16,686
And while you run from your
fears, I can loot the city!

411
00:17:16,719 --> 00:17:18,019
There!

412
00:17:18,052 --> 00:17:20,119
That must be it!

413
00:17:21,752 --> 00:17:22,719
Astro!

414
00:17:25,052 --> 00:17:26,752
Everyone, listen to me!

415
00:17:26,786 --> 00:17:29,986
These monsters are just
illusions. They can't harm you!

416
00:17:33,752 --> 00:17:35,886
He's right!
They went right through him!

417
00:17:35,919 --> 00:17:37,052
There's nothing to be afraid of.

418
00:17:37,086 --> 00:17:38,086
Move out!

419
00:17:38,119 --> 00:17:39,719
Earthquake!

420
00:17:39,752 --> 00:17:42,252
No, it's not.
Someone's down there!

421
00:17:44,052 --> 00:17:45,219
Aha!

422
00:17:49,319 --> 00:17:50,986
Minimini!

423
00:17:52,886 --> 00:17:55,152
Astro! So glad
you could drop in.

424
00:17:55,186 --> 00:17:56,552
The bank just closed!

425
00:17:56,586 --> 00:17:58,519
[LAUGHING]

426
00:17:58,552 --> 00:18:00,552
Not till I make
one last withdrawal.

427
00:18:00,586 --> 00:18:02,186
I'm about to take you out!

428
00:18:03,286 --> 00:18:05,619
Ahhh!

429
00:18:06,886 --> 00:18:08,086
Sorry, Astro,

430
00:18:08,119 --> 00:18:10,552
but this monster
is no illusion.

431
00:18:10,586 --> 00:18:12,086
Huh?

432
00:18:12,119 --> 00:18:13,119
[GRUNTS]

433
00:18:15,052 --> 00:18:16,586
Huh?

434
00:18:16,619 --> 00:18:18,986
Hey, come back!
You can't go in there.

435
00:18:19,019 --> 00:18:19,819
ABERCROMBIE:
Nina!

436
00:18:19,852 --> 00:18:21,086
[SHRIEKS]

437
00:18:21,119 --> 00:18:23,919
[MONSTERS MOANING EERILY]

438
00:18:23,952 --> 00:18:26,119
Oh, no! No!

439
00:18:26,152 --> 00:18:27,152
Ahh!

440
00:18:27,186 --> 00:18:28,652
Nina!

441
00:18:28,686 --> 00:18:30,752
No one's allowed in.
It's too dangerous.

442
00:18:30,786 --> 00:18:32,019
That's my daughter
in there!

443
00:18:32,052 --> 00:18:33,052
Hey!

444
00:18:33,086 --> 00:18:35,286
Nina!
Daddy!

445
00:18:35,319 --> 00:18:36,619
I'm here, Nina.

446
00:18:36,652 --> 00:18:38,019
[BOTH GROAN]

447
00:18:38,052 --> 00:18:39,119
[PANTING]

448
00:18:41,686 --> 00:18:44,152
Nina, tell me,
are you all right?

449
00:18:44,186 --> 00:18:45,186
Uh-huh.

450
00:18:47,319 --> 00:18:50,052
DADDY:
What's that doing here?

451
00:18:50,086 --> 00:18:51,652
What is
it, Daddy?

452
00:18:51,686 --> 00:18:54,752
It's the machine
I had Dr. Minimini build

453
00:18:54,786 --> 00:18:57,219
to make the fairies
in your mind come to life.

454
00:18:58,819 --> 00:19:00,086
You mean
this machine

455
00:19:00,119 --> 00:19:02,752
can really take pictures
of what's in your mind?

456
00:19:02,786 --> 00:19:03,786
Yes,
it--

457
00:19:03,819 --> 00:19:05,486
[BOTH SCREAM]

458
00:19:06,786 --> 00:19:08,552
[SCREAMS]

459
00:19:09,652 --> 00:19:10,786
Daddy!

460
00:19:10,819 --> 00:19:13,086
Daddy, Daddy!

461
00:19:13,119 --> 00:19:14,852
Huh?

462
00:19:14,886 --> 00:19:16,152
What's this?

463
00:19:16,186 --> 00:19:17,752
[ASTRO GRUNTING]

464
00:19:22,586 --> 00:19:23,719
Yeah!

465
00:19:25,586 --> 00:19:26,219
Huh?

466
00:19:29,686 --> 00:19:31,119
[GRUNTS]

467
00:19:31,152 --> 00:19:33,086
[SCREAMS]

468
00:19:38,852 --> 00:19:39,819
These are...

469
00:19:39,852 --> 00:19:42,252
These are all me!

470
00:19:46,186 --> 00:19:47,686
ABERCROMBIE:
Look at them!

471
00:19:47,719 --> 00:19:49,786
They're all
different images of Nina!

472
00:19:49,819 --> 00:19:51,686
[MOANS]

473
00:19:51,719 --> 00:19:52,652
Daddy, Daddy!

474
00:19:52,686 --> 00:19:53,786
Huh?

475
00:19:53,819 --> 00:19:55,052
[GASPS]

476
00:19:55,086 --> 00:19:56,019
Will you
look at that?

477
00:19:56,052 --> 00:19:57,019
It's me!

478
00:19:58,286 --> 00:19:59,886
That's right,
sweetheart.

479
00:19:59,919 --> 00:20:01,252
All my precious
memories of you.

480
00:20:04,552 --> 00:20:06,752
Oh!
Wow!

481
00:20:06,786 --> 00:20:08,786
They're
disappearing!

482
00:20:13,186 --> 00:20:14,986
I'm so sorry, Nina.

483
00:20:15,019 --> 00:20:17,086
I just wanted you
to have your fairies.

484
00:20:17,119 --> 00:20:18,919
Daddy, don't worry.

485
00:20:18,952 --> 00:20:21,252
I found something
much better than fairies.

486
00:20:21,286 --> 00:20:22,286
Oh?

487
00:20:22,319 --> 00:20:23,852
Friends who make me smile.

488
00:20:23,886 --> 00:20:24,886
ASTRO:
Hey, guys!

489
00:20:24,919 --> 00:20:28,252
Astro, you missed
the Nina bubbles.

490
00:20:28,286 --> 00:20:31,052
And whenever kids smile,
fairies are born.

491
00:20:31,086 --> 00:20:33,552
Isn't that right, Friday?

492
00:20:33,586 --> 00:20:35,552
Absolutely, Nina!

493
00:20:41,252 --> 00:20:43,186
[♪]

